{"article_id":"OOBfIDy93gNjbmxv","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN ) --","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The U.S. health system has been preparing since late March for the news","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"we announced Tuesday :","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"the first case of Ebola","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"diagnosed in the United States .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"In this age of global travel , we anticipated","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that a traveler from a country with an Ebola outbreak would come to the United States","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"and develop symptoms","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"once they arrived .","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"But from everything","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"we know now ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"there appears to be no risk","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that anyone on this patient 's flights from Liberia to the United States was exposed to the virus .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Clinicians on the front lines have been one key to our safety :","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"identifying patients with both a history of travel and symptoms","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"indicating","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"they might have Ebola ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"immediately isolating them ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"consulting their local or state health departments ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"and getting the patients tested","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"as needed .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"Indeed ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"since the outbreak began in Africa ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"CDC has consulted with state and local health departments on almost 100 cases","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"in which travelers had recently returned from West Africa","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"and showed symptoms","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"that might have been caused by Ebola .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Of those cases , 14 were considered to be truly at risk .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"Specimens from 13 were tested","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"and Ebola was ruled out in all 13 cases .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"But now CDC labs have confirmed our nation 's first U.S.-diagnosed Ebola patient .","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"I understand","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"this can be deeply troubling news ,","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"especially after what we have witnessed Ebola do in West Africa .","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"But there are distinct differences in what will happen here .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"The United States has a strong health care system and dedicated public health professionals","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"-- all hard at work right now --","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"to make sure","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"this case will not threaten the community at large , or the nation .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"A person","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"who is sick from Ebola virus disease","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"can be cared for in U.S. hospitals","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"when the patient is isolated in a private room with a private bathroom","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"and contact with them is highly controlled .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Every health care worker must meticulously follow every single infection control protection","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"we recommend .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Public health officials , meanwhile , are also identifying people","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"who have had close personal contact with the newly diagnosed patient","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"and will follow up with them for 21 days , the longest known incubation period for Ebola .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"If they develop any signs of the disease ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"those people will be isolated ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"tested","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"and cared for .","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"The fact is that CDC has been preparing for this day ,","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"working around the clock with local and state health departments","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"to enhance surveillance and laboratory testing capacity ,","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"provide recommendations for health care infection control and other measures","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"to prevent disease spread ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"and deliver guidance and tools","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"for health departments","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"to conduct public health investigations .","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"I 'm not going to promise","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"that we can stop this at just one case ,","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"but I can tell you","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"we have the advantage","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"because the right steps are being taken ,","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"and I am therefore confident","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"we will stop Ebola in its tracks here in the United States .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"And there is one final thing","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"to remember ,","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"even as the first case here grabs the headlines :","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"We must be relentless in stopping its spread in West Africa .","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"After all ,","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"after all is said and done here ,","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"that is the only way","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"to truly and completely protect the health security of America","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"-- and the world .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":153,"left":0,"right":152,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":152,"left":128,"right":151,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":106,"right":127,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":106,"left":96,"right":105,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":96,"left":88,"right":95,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":88,"left":80,"right":87,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":80,"left":78,"right":79,"relation":"organization","nuclear